cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the efficiency of deep neural networks in classifying Gaussian mixture models, which is a topic related to machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of neural networks with two hidden layers, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the universality of the Gaussian distribution in feature spaces of data, which is related to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions the use of GMMs in speech, image, and text, which is related to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
